yml File
Alternative to application.properties.
Uses YAML syntax for hierarchical configuration.
Example:spring:
 
  datasource:
 
    url: jdbc:mysql://localhost:3306/db
 
    username: root
 
    password: pass
 
yaml
spring:datasource:url: jdbc:mysql://localhost:3306/dbusername: rootpassword: pass
---------------------------------------------------------
By default, Spring Boot loads application.properties or application.yml from:
src/main/resources/
config/ folder (higher priority)
You can define profile-specific files:
application-dev.properties
application-prod.properties
application-test.properties
-------------------------------------------------------------
 
 
---> When They Are Called
Spring Boot decides which file to load based on the active profile:
Default profile
If no profile is set, it loads application.properties.
Profile-specific
If you set spring.profiles.active=dev, 
then application-dev.properties is loaded in addition to the default application.properties.
Profile-specific values override the defaults.
